<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-11T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-11T13:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2744: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-11T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            11, 1920—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>53. Your December 9, 2 p.m.</p>
                            <p>You may advise the President that the suggestion of the Department
                                was made with the understanding that any new election law which
                                might be passed in the next session of the Nicaraguan Congress would
                                not be construed as being retroactive and would necessarily apply
                                only to future elections.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>